04/09/2007
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- The new commander of KFOR, French General Xavier Bout de Marnhac, met on Monday (September 3rd) with Kosovo President Fatmir Sejdiu, Prime Minister Agim Ceku and Parliament Speaker Kole Berisha. De Marnhac acknowledged that this period of defining Kosovo's final status will bring new security challenges, but he stressed that KFOR and other security forces are ready to respond to any situation. He added that KFOR is prepared to secure the peaceful organisation and conduct of November 17th general elections in the province. 
In other news Monday, Ceku urged the EU to adopt "a more dynamic approach towards Kosovo's independence, or its recognition". Kosovo's status should be "decided immediately", he said, adding that his government is prepared to declare independence unilaterally if necessary. (Telegrafi, RTK, Balkanweb, Kosovalive, Tanjug, Reuters, AP, DPA, AFP - 03/09/07
